# Styling Guide

## Overview

This rule provides comprehensive guidance for styling components and pages in the AlOuf Admin Dashboard. It emphasizes the use of CSS variables for dark mode support, semantic HTML for SEO, and consistent layout patterns throughout the application.

## ⚠️ CRITICAL: RTL-Friendly Classes are Mandatory

**RTL support is the HIGHEST PRIORITY** when dealing with UI. The application supports Arabic (RTL) and English (LTR), and all UI components MUST work correctly in both directions.

### Mandatory RTL-Friendly Classes

**NEVER use these RTL-unfriendly classes:**

- `pl-*`, `pr-*` → Use `ps-*`, `pe-*` instead
- `ml-*`, `mr-*` → Use `ms-*`, `me-*` instead
- `left-*`, `right-*` → Use `start-*`, `end-*` instead
- `text-left`, `text-right` → Use `text-start`, `text-end` instead
- `border-l-*`, `border-r-*` → Use `border-s-*`, `border-e-*` instead
- `rounded-l-*`, `rounded-r-*` → Use `rounded-s-*`, `rounded-e-*` instead

### RTL-Friendly Spacing Pattern

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Logical properties (RTL-aware)
<div className="ms-4 me-2 ps-4 pe-2">  // margin/padding start/end
<div className="start-0 end-0">        // positioning start/end
<div className="text-start">           // text alignment start
<div className="border-s-2 border-e-4"> // border start/end

// ❌ WRONG - Physical properties (break RTL)
<div className="ml-4 mr-2 pl-4 pr-2">  // margin/padding left/right
<div className="left-0 right-0">       // positioning left/right
<div className="text-left">             // text alignment left
<div className="border-l-2 border-r-4"> // border left/right
```

