## CSS Variables and Dark Mode

### Critical Rule: Always Use CSS Variables

**NEVER use hardcoded colors** - Always use CSS variable-based Tailwind classes for colors to ensure dark mode compatibility.

### Available Color Variables

All colors are defined in `styles/globals.css` and automatically switch between light and dark modes:

#### Background Colors

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Uses CSS variables
<div className="bg-card">           // Card background
<div className="bg-background">     // Main background
<div className="bg-muted">          // Muted background
<div className="bg-accent">         // Accent background
<div className="bg-primary">        // Primary background
<div className="bg-secondary">       // Secondary background

// ❌ WRONG - Hardcoded colors (won't work with dark mode)
<div className="bg-white">          // Don't use
<div className="bg-gray-100">       // Don't use
<div className="bg-black">          // Don't use
```

#### Text Colors

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Uses CSS variables
<p className="text-foreground">              // Main text
<p className="text-card-foreground">         // Card text
<p className="text-muted-foreground">       // Muted text
<p className="text-accent-foreground">      // Accent text
<p className="text-primary-foreground">     // Primary text
<p className="text-secondary-foreground">   // Secondary text

// ❌ WRONG - Hardcoded colors
<p className="text-gray-900">               // Don't use
<p className="text-black">                  // Don't use
```

#### Semantic Colors

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Semantic color variables
<div className="bg-success">                    // Success background
<div className="text-success-foreground">       // Success text
<div className="bg-destructive">                // Destructive/error background
<div className="text-destructive-foreground">  // Destructive text
<div className="bg-info-accent">                // Info background
<div className="text-info-foreground">          // Info text

// Status indicators
<span className="bg-success-foreground" />      // Success indicator
<span className="bg-destructive" />            // Error indicator
```

#### Border Colors

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Border variables
<div className="border-border">                // Standard border
<div className="border-input">                 // Input border
<div className="border-t border-border">       // Border top

// ❌ WRONG - Hardcoded borders
<div className="border-gray-200">              // Don't use
<div className="border-black">                // Don't use
```

### Color Variable Reference

**From `styles/globals.css`:**

```css
/* Light Mode */
--background: oklch(1 0 0) /* bg-background */ --foreground: oklch(0.145 0 0)
  /* text-foreground */ --card: oklch(1 0 0) /* bg-card */
  --card-foreground: oklch(0.145 0 0) /* text-card-foreground */
  --muted: oklch(0.97 0 0) /* bg-muted */ --muted-foreground: oklch(0.556 0 0)
  /* text-muted-foreground */ --accent: oklch(0.97 0 0) /* bg-accent */
  --accent-foreground: oklch(0.205 0 0) /* text-accent-foreground */
  --primary: #000000 /* bg-primary */ --primary-foreground: oklch(0.985 0 0)
  /* text-primary-foreground */ --secondary: oklch(0.97 0 0) /* bg-secondary */
  --secondary-foreground: oklch(0.205 0 0) /* text-secondary-foreground */
  --success: oklch(0.6183 0.143 150.63 / 10.2%) /* bg-success */
  --success-foreground: oklch(0.6183 0.143 150.63) /* text-success-foreground */
  --destructive: oklch(0.5963 0.2281 25.71) /* bg-destructive */
  --destructive-foreground: oklch(0.597 0.199 25.61)
  /* text-destructive-foreground */ --border: oklch(0.922 0 0)
  /* border-border */ --input: oklch(0.922 0 0) /* border-input */
