### Using CSS Variables Directly

For custom styling, access CSS variables directly:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Direct CSS variable access
<div style={{ background: 'var(--background)' }}>
<div style={{ color: 'var(--foreground)' }}>
<div style={{ borderColor: 'var(--border)' }}>

// In inline styles or CSS
background: var(--background);
color: var(--foreground);
border-color: var(--border);
```

## HTML Structure and SEO Best Practices

### Semantic HTML Elements

**Always use semantic HTML elements** for better SEO, accessibility, and code clarity:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Semantic HTML
<header>                    // Page header
<nav>                       // Navigation
<main>                      // Main content
<section>                   // Content sections
<article>                   // Article/content
<aside>                     // Sidebar content
<footer>                    // Page footer
<h1>, <h2>, <h3>...        // Heading hierarchy
<p>                         // Paragraphs
<ul>, <ol>                  // Lists
<button>                    // Buttons
<a>                         // Links
<label>                     // Form labels
<form>                      // Forms
<table>                     // Tables

// ❌ WRONG - Generic divs for semantic content
<div className="header">   // Should be <header>
<div className="nav">       // Should be <nav>
<div className="button">    // Should be <button>
```

### Heading Hierarchy

**Maintain proper heading hierarchy** for SEO and accessibility:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Proper heading hierarchy
<PageHeader title="..." />  // Uses <h1> or <h2> internally
<section>
  <Card>
    <CardHeader>
      <CardTitle>Section Title</CardTitle>  // Uses <h3>
    </CardHeader>
    <CardContent>
      <h4>Subsection</h4>                   // <h4>
      <p>Content...</p>
    </CardContent>
  </Card>
</section>

// ❌ WRONG - Skipping heading levels
<h1>Main Title</h1>
<h3>Subtitle</h3>            // Skipped h2 - WRONG
```

### ARIA Labels and Attributes

**Use ARIA attributes** for accessibility:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - ARIA attributes
<nav aria-label="Section stepper">
<button aria-current={active ? 'step' : undefined}>
<div aria-hidden="true">     // Decorative content
<button aria-label="Close dialog">
<form aria-label="Tenant form">

// Semantic elements automatically provide ARIA
<button>                     // Implicit button role
<nav>                        // Implicit navigation role
<form>                       // Implicit form role
```

### Data Attributes

**Use `data-slot` attributes** for component identification:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Data slot attributes
<div data-slot="card">
<div data-slot="card-header">
<div data-slot="card-content">
<button data-slot="button">
```

### Image Alt Text

**Always provide alt text** for images:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Alt text
<NextImage
  alt={title}                    // Descriptive alt text
  src={image}
/>

// ❌ WRONG - Missing or empty alt
<img src={image} />              // Missing alt
<img src={image} alt="" />       // Empty alt (only for decorative)
```

