### Flexbox Patterns

**Common flex patterns:**

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Horizontal flex with icon + text (REQUIRES rtl:flex-row-reverse)
<div className="flex items-center gap-2 rtl:flex-row-reverse">
  <Icon />
  <span>Text</span>
</div>

// ✅ CORRECT - Vertical flex with gap (NO rtl:flex-row-reverse needed)
<div className="flex flex-col gap-5">
  {/* Items */}
</div>

// ✅ CORRECT - Responsive flex with justify-between (NO rtl:flex-row-reverse needed)
<div className="flex flex-col gap-5 md:flex-row md:justify-between">
  {/* Items */}
</div>

// ✅ CORRECT - Full width flex item
<div className="flex-1">
  {/* Takes remaining space */}
</div>
```

**RTL Flex Row Rules:**

- **ALWAYS add `rtl:flex-row-reverse`** to flex rows containing icons, badges, or directional content where visual order matters
- **NEVER add `rtl:flex-row-reverse`** to flex rows with `justify-between`, `justify-center`, or semantic ordering
- Use logical spacing (`gap-*`, `ms-*`, `me-*`) instead of physical spacing (`space-x-*`, `ml-*`, `mr-*`)

### Spacing Patterns

**Consistent spacing with logical properties (RTL-REQUIRED):**

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Standard spacing with logical properties (MANDATORY for RTL)
<div className="m-5">                    // Main margin (20px) - works in both directions
<div className="space-y-5">             // Vertical spacing (logical)
<div className="gap-2">                 // Flex gap (8px) - works in both directions
<div className="gap-3">                 // Flex gap (12px)
<div className="gap-5">                 // Flex gap (20px)
<div className="p-5">                   // Padding (20px) - works in both directions

// ✅ CORRECT - Logical margin/padding properties (RTL-REQUIRED)
<div className="ms-4">                  // margin-start (left in LTR, right in RTL) - REQUIRED
<div className="me-4">                  // margin-end (right in LTR, left in RTL) - REQUIRED
<div className="ps-4">                  // padding-start (left in LTR, right in RTL) - REQUIRED
<div className="pe-4">                  // padding-end (right in LTR, left in RTL) - REQUIRED

// ❌ WRONG - Directional properties (BREAK RTL - NEVER USE)
<div className="ml-4">                  // margin-left - NEVER USE
<div className="mr-4">                  // margin-right - NEVER USE
<div className="pl-4">                  // padding-left - NEVER USE
<div className="pr-4">                  // padding-right - NEVER USE
<div className="space-x-2">             // horizontal spacing - use gap-* instead

// Common spacing scale
gap-1   // 4px
gap-2   // 8px
gap-3   // 12px
gap-4   // 16px
gap-5   // 20px
```

## Responsive Design

### Breakpoint Strategy

**Use Tailwind breakpoints:**

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Mobile-first responsive
<div className="flex flex-col gap-5 md:flex-row md:justify-between">
<div className="hidden lg:block">        // Hide on mobile, show on large
<div className="w-full md:w-1/2">        // Full width on mobile, half on medium
<div className="text-sm md:text-base">  // Smaller text on mobile

// Breakpoints
sm:  640px   // Small devices
md:  768px   // Medium devices
lg:  1024px  // Large devices
xl:  1280px  // Extra large devices
2xl: 1536px  // 2x Extra large devices
```

### RTL Support (CRITICAL REQUIREMENT)

**RTL support is MANDATORY. All UI components MUST work correctly in both LTR and RTL.**

**Use logical properties (REQUIRED):**

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Use logical properties (works automatically in both LTR and RTL)
<div className="flex gap-2">
  {/* gap-* automatically handles both directions */}
</div>

// ✅ CORRECT - Logical spacing properties (MANDATORY)
<div className="me-4 pe-2 border-e">
  {/* me-* (margin-end), pe-* (padding-end), border-e (border-end) */}
</div>

// ✅ CORRECT - Logical positioning (MANDATORY)
<div className="absolute start-0 end-0">
  {/* start-* and end-* work in both directions */}
</div>

// ✅ CORRECT - Logical text alignment (MANDATORY)
<div className="text-start">
  {/* text-start works in both directions */}
</div>

// ❌ WRONG - Directional properties break RTL (NEVER USE)
<div className={cn(
  isRTL ? 'pl-4' : 'pr-4'  // Don't use conditional directional classes
)}>
<div className="ml-4 mr-2">  // Don't use physical properties
<div className="left-0 right-0">  // Don't use physical positioning
<div className="text-left">  // Don't use physical text alignment

// ✅ CORRECT - Use logical properties instead
<div className="ps-4">  {/* padding-start works in both LTR and RTL */}
<div className="ms-4 me-2">  {/* margin-start/end works in both directions */}
<div className="start-0 end-0">  {/* start/end works in both directions */}
<div className="text-start">  {/* text-start works in both directions */}
```

**For flex layouts that need to reverse in RTL:**

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Use flex-row-reverse for RTL
<div className="flex items-center gap-2 rtl:flex-row-reverse">
  <Icon />
  <span>Text</span>
</div>
```

**For directional icons:**

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Rotate icons for RTL
<ChevronRight className="rtl:rotate-180" />
<ChevronLeft className="rtl:rotate-180" />
```

## Complete RTL Migration Guide

### Phase 1: Identify RTL-Unfriendly Classes

Search for these patterns across all `.tsx`, `.ts`, and `.css` files:

```bash
# Physical padding classes
pl-*, pr-*

# Physical margin classes
ml-*, mr-*

# Physical positioning
left-*, right-*

# Physical text alignment
text-left, text-right

# Physical borders
border-l-*, border-r-*, rounded-l-*, rounded-r-*, rounded-tl-*, rounded-tr-*, rounded-bl-*, rounded-br-*

# Physical float
float-left, float-right

# Physical scroll
scroll-ml-*, scroll-mr-*, scroll-pl-*, scroll-pr-*
```

### Phase 2: Complete Migration Mapping

#### Padding Classes

| ❌ RTL-Unfriendly | ✅ RTL-Friendly | Notes                                 |
| ----------------- | --------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| `pl-{size}`       | `ps-{size}`     | padding-inline-start                  |
| `pr-{size}`       | `pe-{size}`     | padding-inline-end                    |
| `px-{size}`       | `px-{size}`     | Already RTL-friendly (padding-inline) |
| `py-{size}`       | `py-{size}`     | Already RTL-friendly (padding-block)  |

**Examples:**

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG
<div className="pl-4 pr-6">Content</div>

// ✅ CORRECT
<div className="ps-4 pe-6">Content</div>
```

#### Margin Classes

| ❌ RTL-Unfriendly | ✅ RTL-Friendly | Notes                                |
| ----------------- | --------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| `ml-{size}`       | `ms-{size}`     | margin-inline-start                  |
| `mr-{size}`       | `me-{size}`     | margin-inline-end                    |
| `mx-{size}`       | `mx-{size}`     | Already RTL-friendly (margin-inline) |
| `my-{size}`       | `my-{size}`     | Already RTL-friendly (margin-block)  |

**Examples:**

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG
<div className="ml-2 mr-4">Content</div>
<button className="ml-auto">Button</button>

// ✅ CORRECT
<div className="ms-2 me-4">Content</div>
<button className="ms-auto">Button</button>
```

#### Positioning Classes

| ❌ RTL-Unfriendly | ✅ RTL-Friendly  | Notes                           |
| ----------------- | ---------------- | ------------------------------- |
| `left-{size}`     | `start-{size}`   | inset-inline-start              |
| `right-{size}`    | `end-{size}`     | inset-inline-end                |
| `inset-x-{size}`  | `inset-x-{size}` | Already RTL-friendly            |
| `inset-y-{size}`  | `inset-y-{size}` | Already RTL-friendly            |
| `top-{size}`      | `top-{size}`     | Already RTL-friendly (vertical) |
| `bottom-{size}`   | `bottom-{size}`  | Already RTL-friendly (vertical) |

**Examples:**

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG
<div className="absolute left-0 right-0">Content</div>
<div className="fixed left-4">Sidebar</div>

// ✅ CORRECT
<div className="absolute start-0 end-0">Content</div>
<div className="fixed start-4">Sidebar</div>
```

#### Border Classes

| ❌ RTL-Unfriendly   | ✅ RTL-Friendly     | Notes                     |
| ------------------- | ------------------- | ------------------------- |
| `border-l-{size}`   | `border-s-{size}`   | border-inline-start-width |
| `border-r-{size}`   | `border-e-{size}`   | border-inline-end-width   |
| `border-l-{color}`  | `border-s-{color}`  | border-inline-start-color |
| `border-r-{color}`  | `border-e-{color}`  | border-inline-end-color   |
| `border-x-{size}`   | `border-x-{size}`   | Already RTL-friendly      |
| `border-y-{size}`   | `border-y-{size}`   | Already RTL-friendly      |
| `rounded-l-{size}`  | `rounded-s-{size}`  | border-start-radius       |
| `rounded-r-{size}`  | `rounded-e-{size}`  | border-end-radius         |
| `rounded-tl-{size}` | `rounded-ss-{size}` | border-start-start-radius |
| `rounded-tr-{size}` | `rounded-se-{size}` | border-start-end-radius   |
| `rounded-bl-{size}` | `rounded-es-{size}` | border-end-start-radius   |
| `rounded-br-{size}` | `rounded-ee-{size}` | border-end-end-radius     |

**Examples:**

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG
<div className="border-l-2 border-r-4 border-l-primary rounded-l-lg">Content</div>

// ✅ CORRECT
<div className="border-s-2 border-e-4 border-s-primary rounded-s-lg">Content</div>
```

#### Text Alignment Classes

| ❌ RTL-Unfriendly | ✅ RTL-Friendly | Notes                |
| ----------------- | --------------- | -------------------- |
| `text-left`       | `text-start`    | text-align: start    |
| `text-right`      | `text-end`      | text-align: end      |
| `text-center`     | `text-center`   | Already RTL-friendly |

**Examples:**

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG
<div className="text-left">Content</div>
<div className="text-right">Content</div>

// ✅ CORRECT
<div className="text-start">Content</div>
<div className="text-end">Content</div>
```

#### Float Classes

| ❌ RTL-Unfriendly | ✅ RTL-Friendly | Notes               |
| ----------------- | --------------- | ------------------- |
| `float-left`      | `float-start`   | float: inline-start |
| `float-right`     | `float-end`     | float: inline-end   |

**Examples:**

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG
<img className="float-left" src="..." />

// ✅ CORRECT
<img className="float-start" src="..." />
```

#### Scroll Classes

| ❌ RTL-Unfriendly  | ✅ RTL-Friendly    | Notes                       |
| ------------------ | ------------------ | --------------------------- |
| `scroll-ml-{size}` | `scroll-ms-{size}` | scroll-margin-inline-start  |
| `scroll-mr-{size}` | `scroll-me-{size}` | scroll-margin-inline-end    |
| `scroll-pl-{size}` | `scroll-ps-{size}` | scroll-padding-inline-start |
| `scroll-pr-{size}` | `scroll-pe-{size}` | scroll-padding-inline-end   |
| `scroll-mx-{size}` | `scroll-mx-{size}` | Already RTL-friendly        |
| `scroll-px-{size}` | `scroll-px-{size}` | Already RTL-friendly        |

**Examples:**

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG
<div className="scroll-ml-4 scroll-pl-2">Content</div>

// ✅ CORRECT
<div className="scroll-ms-4 scroll-ps-2">Content</div>
```

### Phase 3: Special Cases

#### Conditional RTL Classes

**❌ NEVER use conditional RTL classes:**

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG - Don't use conditional classes
<div className={cn(isRTL ? 'pl-4' : 'pr-4')}>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't use ltr: and rtl: variants for spacing
<div className="ltr:mr-2 rtl:ml-2">
```

**✅ ALWAYS use logical properties:**

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Use logical properties that work automatically
<div className="ps-4">  {/* Works in both LTR and RTL */}
<div className="ms-2">  {/* Works in both LTR and RTL */}
```

#### Flexbox Layouts

**When to use `rtl:flex-row-reverse`:**

**✅ REQUIRED - Use `rtl:flex-row-reverse` for:**

- Flex rows with icons + text (icon should be on right in RTL)
- Menu items, navigation items, buttons with icons
- Badges or labels with icons
- Any flex row where visual order matters and should flip in RTL
- **Responsive flex patterns** that become rows at certain breakpoints (e.g., `lg:flex-row` should also get `lg:rtl:flex-row-reverse` if it contains icons+text)

**❌ NOT NEEDED - Don't use `rtl:flex-row-reverse` for:**

- Flex rows with `justify-between` (space distribution, order doesn't matter)
- Flex rows with `justify-center` (centered content)
- Flex rows where order is semantic (form fields, data display)
- Flex rows where items are positioned using logical properties (`ms-auto`, `me-auto`)

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Icon + text pattern (REQUIRES rtl:flex-row-reverse)
<div className="flex items-center gap-2 rtl:flex-row-reverse">
  <Icon />
  <span>Text</span>
</div>

// ✅ CORRECT - Menu item with icon (REQUIRES rtl:flex-row-reverse)
<Link className="flex items-center gap-2 rtl:flex-row-reverse">
  <Icon />
  <span>Menu Item</span>
</Link>

// ✅ CORRECT - Button with icon (REQUIRES rtl:flex-row-reverse)
<Button className="flex items-center gap-2 rtl:flex-row-reverse">
  <Icon />
  <span>Action</span>
</Button>

// ✅ CORRECT - Responsive flex with icon+text (REQUIRES responsive rtl:flex-row-reverse)
<div className="flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-1.5 p-4 xl:flex-row xl:justify-start xl:rtl:flex-row-reverse">
  <Icon className="text-destructive me-2 h-5 w-5" />
  <div className="flex flex-col">
    <span className="text-muted-foreground text-xs font-normal">{label}</span>
    <span className="text-foreground text-sm font-medium">{value}</span>
  </div>
</div>

// ✅ CORRECT - Responsive flex row pattern (REQUIRES matching responsive rtl:flex-row-reverse)
<div className="flex flex-col gap-2 md:flex-row md:rtl:flex-row-reverse">
  <Icon />
  <span>Text</span>
</div>

// ✅ CORRECT - justify-between (NO rtl:flex-row-reverse needed)
<div className="flex items-center justify-between">
  <span>Left</span>
  <span>Right</span>
</div>

// ✅ CORRECT - justify-center (NO rtl:flex-row-reverse needed)
<div className="flex items-center justify-center gap-2">
  <span>Centered</span>
</div>
```

