#### Search Patterns

Use these grep patterns to find RTL-unfriendly classes:

```bash
# Padding
grep -r "pl-[0-9]\|pr-[0-9]" --include="*.tsx" --include="*.ts"

# Margin
grep -r "ml-[0-9]\|mr-[0-9]" --include="*.tsx" --include="*.ts"

# Positioning
grep -r "left-[0-9]\|right-[0-9]" --include="*.tsx" --include="*.ts"

# Text alignment
grep -r "text-left\|text-right" --include="*.tsx" --include="*.ts"

# Borders
grep -r "border-l-\|border-r-\|rounded-l-\|rounded-r-\|rounded-tl-\|rounded-tr-\|rounded-bl-\|rounded-br-" --include="*.tsx" --include="*.ts"

# Float
grep -r "float-left\|float-right" --include="*.tsx" --include="*.ts"

# Responsive flex-row patterns that might need rtl:flex-row-reverse
