## Best Practices

1. ✅ **RTL-FRIENDLY CLASSES ARE MANDATORY** - Always use logical properties (`ps-*`, `pe-*`, `ms-*`, `me-*`, `start-*`, `end-*`, `text-start`, `text-end`, `border-s-*`, `border-e-*`) - See Complete RTL Migration Guide section above
2. ✅ **Always use CSS variable-based Tailwind classes** for colors
3. ✅ **Use semantic HTML elements** (header, nav, main, section, article, etc.)
4. ✅ **Maintain proper heading hierarchy** (h1 → h2 → h3...)
5. ✅ **Provide alt text** for all images
6. ✅ **Use ARIA attributes** for accessibility
7. ✅ **Use `m-5`** for main content containers
8. ✅ **Use `space-y-5`** for vertical spacing
9. ✅ **Use `gap-2`, `gap-3`, `gap-5`** for flex gaps (not `space-x-*`)
10. ✅ **Use logical properties** (`me-*`, `ms-*`, `pe-*`, `ps-*`, `border-e`, `border-s`) instead of directional (`mr-*`, `ml-*`, `pr-*`, `pl-*`, `border-r`, `border-l`)
11. ✅ **Mobile-first responsive design** with Tailwind breakpoints
12. ✅ **Support RTL layouts** for Arabic locale (logical properties handle this automatically)
13. ✅ **Use `cn()` utility** for conditional classes
14. ✅ **Use component variants** (Button, Card, Badge, etc.)
15. ✅ **Maintain consistent spacing** (use spacing scale)
16. ✅ **Use semantic color names** (success, destructive, muted, etc.)
17. ✅ **Never hardcode colors** - always use CSS variables
18. ✅ **Never use directional spacing** (`ml-*`, `mr-*`, `pl-*`, `pr-*`, `space-x-*`) - use logical properties instead

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

1. ❌ **NEVER use RTL-unfriendly classes** (`pl-*`, `pr-*`, `ml-*`, `mr-*`, `left-*`, `right-*`, `text-left`, `text-right`, `border-l-*`, `border-r-*`, `rounded-l-*`, `rounded-r-*`) - Use logical properties instead - See Complete RTL Migration Guide section above
2. ❌ **Don't use hardcoded colors** (`bg-white`, `text-black`, `bg-gray-100`)
3. ❌ **Don't use generic divs** for semantic content (`<div className="header">` → use `<header>`)
4. ❌ **Don't skip heading levels** (`h1` → `h3` is wrong, should be `h1` → `h2`)
5. ❌ **Don't forget alt text** on images
6. ❌ **Don't use arbitrary values** when standard utilities exist (`p-[20px]` → use `p-5`)
7. ❌ **Don't mix spacing systems** (stick to Tailwind spacing scale)
8. ❌ **Don't use inline styles** for colors (use CSS variables)
9. ❌ **Don't use directional spacing properties** (`ml-*`, `mr-*`, `pl-*`, `pr-*`, `space-x-*`, `border-l`, `border-r`) - use logical properties (`ms-*`, `me-*`, `ps-*`, `pe-*`, `gap-*`, `border-s`, `border-e`) instead
10. ❌ **Don't use conditional RTL classes** (`isRTL ? 'pl-4' : 'pr-4'`) - use logical properties (`ps-4`) that work automatically

## CSS Variable Reference

### Complete Variable List

**Backgrounds:**

- `bg-background` → `var(--background)`
- `bg-card` → `var(--card)`
- `bg-muted` → `var(--muted)`
- `bg-accent` → `var(--accent)`
- `bg-primary` → `var(--primary)`
- `bg-secondary` → `var(--secondary)`
- `bg-success` → `var(--success)`
- `bg-destructive` → `var(--destructive)`

**Text:**

- `text-foreground` → `var(--foreground)`
- `text-card-foreground` → `var(--card-foreground)`
- `text-muted-foreground` → `var(--muted-foreground)`
- `text-accent-foreground` → `var(--accent-foreground)`
- `text-primary-foreground` → `var(--primary-foreground)`
- `text-secondary-foreground` → `var(--secondary-foreground)`
- `text-success-foreground` → `var(--success-foreground)`
- `text-destructive-foreground` → `var(--destructive-foreground)`

**Borders:**

- `border-border` → `var(--border)`
- `border-input` → `var(--input)`

**Radius:**

- `rounded-md` → `var(--radius-md)`
- `rounded-lg` → `var(--radius-lg)`
- `rounded-xl` → `var(--radius-xl)`

See [code-comments.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/_common/code-comments.mdc) for code commenting standards.

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Comment explains complex logic
// Calculate RTL-aware offset: negative for LTR, positive for RTL
const offset = direction === 'rtl' ? -scrollAmount : scrollAmount

// ❌ WRONG - Obvious comment that restates code
// Set the offset to scrollAmount
const offset = scrollAmount
```

This styling guide ensures consistent, accessible, SEO-friendly, and dark-mode-compatible styling throughout the application.
